			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Yes, this is the solution to all our problems. Don't believe me? Well, u came this far and I have your attention, lets progress and take a quick look at the Mage.........
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Levels 1 - 50.
<br />

<br />
Remember these levels? In my opinion, the mage was and still is totally competent in these levels. In fact, it has got easier for the new up and coming Mage.. How?
<br />
Well, remember before? (based on soloing).. Pull mob - pet attack mob - mage med (book open!), nuke, med, nuke, nuke.-- mob dead. Woot, thrilling stuff ! The mage couldn't sit all the time, cos the mage had to OUTDAMAGE the pet to get the XP!
<br />
Now, its more, pull - pet attack - med, nuke , med............ nuke.. Mob dead!! woot ....
<br />

<br />
Summary.. 1-50, fairly easy and a lot easier now, IMO.
<br />

<br />
51 - 60
<br />

<br />
Gets a little tougher now for the mage, but with some of the old world zones revamped, xp isnt that hard to come by IMO. Plus the mage gets that added spell line up from levelling, plus the mage now has a new utility at hand.. AA's !!! 
<br />
Also with DPoC (the Ldon Focus item), which increases the pet quite a bit IMO for this level range, and isnt that hard to get, even for the casual player.
<br />
(slight note here, not sure if it affects the older pets.. Never tried..sorry. But it is available or a version of focii is available).
<br />

<br />
Summary  51-60, if you don't include POP zones and do include items that you could obtain, either from Bazaar or with friends help etc... I think its not that hard to obtain a good constant xp gain through them.
<br />

<br />
levels 61+
<br />

<br />
Now this is really where the magician lacks IMO, mainly due to our pet, afterall, we are a pet class that totally relys on that summoned Jabober.. Our pet can give us xp in those old worlds, try PoHate, its not that bad up there at all... But due to our level now, the xp gained in most places, is quite pathetic, mainly because we can't get in to those high xp places like PoP zones, cos our pet gets ripped apart before we can effectively kill the mob. Even the "uba" Time focused pets stand really no chance, against these kind of hard hitting mobs. (Not that I really know, but thats my understanding from posts in these forums).
<br />

<br />
Summary 61+
<br />

<br />
Magician lacks in solo for sure; Grouping isnt bad, but no utulity from pet to off tank; Raids, pet gets eaten by waves of aoe...
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
I don't think many of you can dispute the above; yes not perfect but its the <span style="text-decoration: underline">Picture</span> I want you to see, not the actual execution of this and that.. Yes, some ppl can solo X mob in PoI or tactics or blah blah, but not v effeciently IMO.
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">So the Solution</span>
<br />

<br />
ok, now you can go OH NO!!!!
<br />

<br />
New Magician only AA Skill....!!!!!! (plz read on <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" /> )
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Innate Pet Regen !!
<br />

<br />
5 Levels of Skill.
<br />
Starts at 51, then 55,59,62,65.... 
<br />
Costs 2,3,3,4,4. (16aa)
<br />

<br />
Effect : 
<br />
Adds 100/tick regen to pet per skill level.
<br />
(ie at lvl 3 of it, you would get 300/tick regen)
<br />

<br />
Important BIT..
<br />

<br />
Stacks with FOCII... and is a FIGHTING regen, not a SITTING regen.
<br />

<br />
Get the idea?
<br />

<br />
1. It would help soloing Magi from lvl 51 onwards.
<br />
2. It would help grouping Magi off tank that add.
<br />
3. It would help raiding Magi keep their pet alive during those nasty AOE's, with help from Calliav line.
<br />

<br />
It's not gonna be the answer to suit everyone I am sure, but i think you will have to agree, that it is pretty damn close, and with the other GoD pet aa's will help the 3 wise Magi above in nearly all occasions.
<br />

<br />
It's not hard to implement either, not hard to obtain, doesn't need extortionate amounts of aa, doesn't require more spells to obtain, doesn't require ultra rare drops blah blah....
<br />

<br />
Thank you very much for your time and I hope that we can all agree that this would be a MAJOR upgrade for us without overpowering us. 
<br />

<br />
(Numbers given are my estimates but I think that they are reasonable and close to what they should be)
<br />

<br />
I hope this wasn't covered on a thread somewhere that I have not read.. If so, I apologise now for repeating, if not, I hope we can all agree, that it would work and would be achievable by us, The Magi and by SoE (VI etc) to implement.
<br />

<br />
Again, thanks for reading.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline"></span><br />_________________<br />Stonio Gryffindor
