				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">same complaint i have to some degree.. 
<br />
Idealy SOE has to balance what they can give with what can be exploited.  They give an item to someone (class) and they have to be sure that it cant be hugely exploited.
<br />
My solution?
<br />
Mage summoned pet weps and items as follows.
<br />

<br />
1hb   
<br />
35/20
<br />
lvl 55 reqired
<br />
class: all
<br />
race: summoned
<br />

<br />
this would limit the wepon to a sumoned being and 55+ thus lvl 60+ mage pets only.
<br />
the pet has a "summoned" tag somewhere in it's code so putting that as a race or something would allow the item to be freely given out and only used on mage pets.  The possible exploit here would be if someone charmed a summoned mob but from what i've seen most all summoned mobs in POP that are 55+ mostly are tagged uncharmable already.
<br />

<br />
you could have a armor item also with those same restrictions that would give your pet like 30% more HP and AC.
<br />

<br />
another option is to tag mage pets as a summoned type II mob (it's own class or race) to furthur limit any possibility of exploits.
<br />

<br />
I personally would also like to see mages get an AA CH pet and a 65 lvl heal that would heal the pet like 40%
<br />
also I think we should get some AA's usefull for us that raid.. since MGB and songs don't hit our pet... maybe some AA's that give the pet 500DR for 1,2,3 min at each lvl.  Most battles last more than 3 min and the pet would get hozed when it wore off but i hate seeing our pets get raped by AE rampage and AOE's that do 2k+ per round.
<br />

<br />
but like that will ever happon.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
