Answers ur question about how much it regens, if its too much, its altered down to like 75 a level. 
<br />

<br />
As I keep repeating, its the simplicity of the idea, not the actual execution thats important.
<br />

<br />
Needs tuning, I am sure, but find me another simple way to do it?
<br />

<br />
So far ive seen, new spells, abilities asked for that we wont ever get and the such like. This is easy, helps a Vast array of Magi in a vast array of encounters. Instead of "oh this overpowers us", a reply of, "well, 100 is a bit much, but 50 or 60 might work" is far more productive than just shaking ur head.
<br />

<br />
As to the 61 war with 16aa, a war isnt a Soloer by any means. If a wiz, Necro, Enchanter can already do this with their play style, then the basis that a magi pet shouldn't be better as a tank to fit our play style, isn't a fair comparison. The wiz has the same thing, except the tank doesn't exist, he just snares/roots. We wont get snare/root (unless u are a v lucky person to have the earring they nerfed), so the comparison isn't justified. A pet wont ever take the place of a tank in a grp, WHY? Cos anyone else going near the mob gets agro, only case I can see that working is in all pet grps.. Which isnt a problem since an all pet grp can do it regardless if they are 60 tanks or 61 tanks with regen... so that issue is already pointless.
<br />

<br />
You make comparisons that are not relevant IMO, cos they either already exist or are not feasible. We go toe to toe with mobs, its the Mage way, but without a chance in hell to heal/nuke, we wont ever win. This bides us time to do that, which is what we need.
<br />

<br />
